\title{Sentence as smallest unit}
\date{2024-04-03}

\p{We are used to thinking of complete sentences as composed of parts, but an alternative point of view takes sentences to be the more primitive unit.
}

\p{[Kant](kant): [Judgment as prior to concepts](phil-016V)}

\p{Late [Wittgenstein](wittgenstein): sentence as smallest linguistic unit one can use to make a move in a language game.}

\p{[Frege](frege): sentence as smallest unit to which pragmatic force can attach.}